[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
CWR-CE installs the engine binaries (PoseidonGame, PoseidonServer,
PoseidonStudio, PoseidonTools, PoseidonTetris, PoseidonGameDemo) but
no game data. The original "Arma: Cold War Assault" assets are required
to run anything beyond Tetris and are NOT redistributable.

If you own the game (e.g. via GOG), install the data with:

    pkg install innoextract
    install-cwr-data /path/to/setup_arma_cold_war_assault_*.exe

This unpacks DTA/, AddOns/, BIN/, Campaigns/, Worlds/, ... into
~/.local/share/CWR/base/ in the layout the engine expects. Pass
--dest <dir> to install elsewhere, or --help for the full usage.

Then launch the game with:

    cwr-ce

The launcher resolves the data root and passes it to PoseidonGame.
If you installed the data elsewhere, set $CWR_DATA before launching:

    CWR_DATA=/path/to/data-root cwr-ce

Any extra arguments are forwarded to PoseidonGame (see --help).

EOM
}
]
